.TH SUTURE-CHECKOUT "1" "April 2026" "Suture v5.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
suture\-checkout \- Switch to a different branch
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B suture checkout [\\fIoptions\\fR] [\\fIbranch\\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Switch to a different branch.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \\\-b, \\\-\\\-new\-branch \\fI<name>\\fR
Create a new branch before switching
.TP
.BR \\\-C \\fI<REPO_PATH>\\fR
Run as if suture was started in <path>
.TP
.BR \\\-h, \\\-\\\-help
Print help
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
suture checkout main       # Switch to "main" branch
suture checkout \\\-b feature # Create and switch to "feature"
suture checkout \\\-b feat main  # Create "feat" from "main"
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR suture (1)
